The paper deals with problems related to arrangements of lines in the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problems involve coloring and guarding cells of the arrangement, which are combinatorial in nature and can be formulated as hypergraph problems (cs.DM). The paper also gives bounds on the chromatic number and the size of minimum vertex covers, which are fundamental graph-theoretic concepts (cs.DS, cs.GT). Finally, the paper uses techniques from approximation algorithms and discrete mathematics (cs.CC) to derive the bounds.
